Would be super simple, essentially wrap a module into `(x, f) => f(x)` where `f(x)` is `true` or `f(x)` is `false`. `x` can then be something like 

``` javascript
require('is-my-schema-valid')({
  required: true,
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
    rna-fastq: {
      required: true,
      type: RegExp
      pattern: new RegExp(`^${speciesName}.${run}.fastq.gz`)
    }
  }
})
```

However just realized perhaps [is-my-schema-valid](https://github.com/mafintosh/is-my-json-valid) cannot compare `RegExp` objects as they are not by default in `JSON.stringify()`. @mafintosh, how difficult to extend the plugin, perhaps similar like `replacer` and `reviver` functions to faciltate comparisons of objects?

Taking a hint from how webpack lets you choose _loaders_ based on regexing (somewhat implicit understood) filetypes, could apply arrows of validators to specific files, or subtrees of resolved output objects.
